item.description:
Wimpyâ€™s Seafood Cafe, which acquired its name from the loveable hamburger eating character on the cartoon Popeye, was established in 1938 as a small hamburger stand. Over the years the restaurant has grown by over 200 seats with the addition of a traditional tavern and two fireside dining rooms.

Wimpy's offers a full brunch menu including eggs, omelets, quiche and several varieties of Eggs Benedict. They also have a full service bar for brunch cocktails.
